  "abstract": "The objectives of this workshop, Farmers' participatory management of diseases\r\nfor higher yield and nutritive value of crop residues of groundnut, Deccan Plateau,\r\nIndia, are to critically review the results of the studies conducted over the last two\r\nyears and ascertain how to make best use of the findings. Held at the Agricultural\r\nResearch Station (ARS), Acharya NG Ranga Agricultural University (ANGRAU) ,\r\nAnantapur, Andhra Pradesh, the workshop was sponsored by ICRISAT, the\r\nInternational Livestock Research Institute (ILRI), ANGRAU, and funded by the\r\nDepartment for International Development (DFID) , UK.",
